1
00:00:17,168 --> 00:00:20,568
<font color="#ffff00">The New York Superspeed with service from Salt Lake ..</font>

2
00:00:20,611 --> 00:00:23,078
<font color="#ffff00">Denver, Kansas City and Point East ..</font>

3
00:00:23,441 --> 00:00:26,885
<font color="#ffff00">is now arriving on track 1.</font>

4
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:47,497
<font color="#ff8040">DESERT HEARTS</font>

5
00:01:52,235 --> 00:01:53,979
Beg you pardon.

6
00:01:54,125 --> 00:01:58,697
<font color="#ffff00">Passengers continuing on the super speed
service to Sacramento and Oakland...</font>

7
00:01:58,896 --> 00:02:01,093
<font color="#ffff00">can now be on board.</font>

8
00:02:05,863 --> 00:02:08,092
-Can I help you, miss?
-Please.

9
00:02:08,747 --> 00:02:10,950
-I'll bring this for you.
-Thank you.

10
00:02:18,673 --> 00:02:20,188
Professor Bell?

11
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:24,492
- Call me Vivian.
- Welcome to Reno.

12
00:02:25,006 --> 00:02:26,429
I am down the street that way.

13
00:02:27,483 --> 00:02:29,437
- Hi Frances.
- Hello, Burnett.

14
00:02:29,842 --> 00:02:32,412
- I have space in my car.
- No, not such luck.

15
00:02:35,023 --> 00:02:38,333
Well, looking forward
to some good desert living?

16
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:41,661
I'm looking forward to get these shoes of.

17
00:02:41,973 --> 00:02:44,513
It's awful when your legs hurts.

18
00:02:44,973 --> 00:02:47,217
It's a kindest thing
I've heard in three days.

19
00:02:48,353 --> 00:02:51,306
- How long have you been married honey?
- 12 years.

20
00:02:52,064 --> 00:02:54,523
Oh, no,no. we handle all that.

21
00:02:54,817 --> 00:02:57,636
Quint, that's the lucky one.

22
00:02:58,036 --> 00:02:59,746
Sure could have used it  last night.

23
00:03:09,854 --> 00:03:11,674
See you in six weeks, madam.

24
00:03:11,737 --> 00:03:14,915
Soon as we are out of this place you
can tell me all about yourself.

25
00:03:17,965 --> 00:03:23,716
I used to be a feature dancer in
that casino over there, 100 years ago.

26
00:03:27,992 --> 00:03:29,639
You got any kids?

27
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:32,798
We were a professional couple.

28
00:03:35,444 --> 00:03:40,366
My man was a professional too
he was a prominent attorney here in town.

29
00:03:41,729 --> 00:03:45,224
- Went with a heart attack at 41.
- Sorry.

30
00:03:47,622 --> 00:03:49,221
How long have you been alone?

31
00:03:49,401 --> 00:03:52,427
I'm not alone, I got my boy with me.

32
00:03:54,603 --> 00:03:57,728
My girl works right over
there at the Golden Ring.

33
00:03:58,917 --> 00:04:03,669
She's got Glen's wild streak
running right thru her.

34
00:04:05,848 --> 00:04:07,669
I have always lived in the city.

35
00:04:08,644 --> 00:04:11,056
I Don't know what to do
with all this space.

36
00:04:11,813 --> 00:04:14,165
I think of it as a God's backyard.

37
00:04:15,383 --> 00:04:18,805
Just sit back and let
it clean out the impurities.

38
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:22,778
-And the heat?
-Lots of ice tea and no deep thinking.

39
00:04:23,991 --> 00:04:25,813
I'll buy that.

40
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:29,372
Oh, brother!

41
00:04:39,674 --> 00:04:43,000
-What are you doing at this hour?
- I have things to do.

42
00:04:44,078 --> 00:04:47,407
-Professor Bell, Cay Rivvers.
-How do you do.

43
00:04:50,789 --> 00:04:53,877
-Shall I call you professor?
-Vivian Bell.

44
00:04:55,371 --> 00:04:58,222
Put that damned car forward!

45
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:03,568
Jesus!

46
00:05:04,701 --> 00:05:06,736
Three guesses who that was.

47
00:05:07,409 --> 00:05:09,857
- Do you mind if I smoke?
- Sure don't.

48
00:05:11,147 --> 00:05:13,351
Never would have guessed you smoked.

49
00:05:15,326 --> 00:05:17,016
Can I be honest with you, Frances?

50
00:05:17,756 --> 00:05:20,065
It's a dying art.
So be my guest.

51
00:05:22,986 --> 00:05:26,872
Things are .. a little bit shaky
for me at the moment.

52
00:05:28,593 --> 00:05:32,980
-Appreciate for sharing that.
-I really can't be part of the gang right now.

53
00:05:36,819 --> 00:05:38,186
Just leave it to me.

54
00:05:39,202 --> 00:05:40,562
Thanks.

55
00:06:23,667 --> 00:06:26,410
Walter, we're here!

56
00:06:31,011 --> 00:06:35,609
Walter, shake hands
with professor Vivian.

57
00:06:35,842 --> 00:06:37,139
-Hi.
-Hello.

58
00:06:37,787 --> 00:06:41,923
-You are younger than I expected.
-I'll take that as a compliment.

59
00:06:42,932 --> 00:06:44,356
Get the bags, Walter.

60
00:06:48,359 --> 00:06:50,027
You gonna love it here.

61
00:06:58,671 --> 00:07:01,270
Well, here it is.

62
00:07:02,387 --> 00:07:03,440
Nice, he?

63
00:07:05,145 --> 00:07:07,460
It's lovely.

64
00:07:07,559 --> 00:07:10,367
-Oh, Walter will take you to your room.
-Thank you.

65
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:27,112
-The bathroom is over there.
-Thank you.

66
00:07:27,883 --> 00:07:29,381
What do you teach?

67
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:32,142
I teach English literature
at Columbia University.

68
00:07:32,877 --> 00:07:35,996
116th Street, Broadway,
New York, New York.

69
00:07:41,721 --> 00:07:45,803
I know you want me to hang around and
give you a history of the ranch.

70
00:07:46,110 --> 00:07:47,678
How did you guess, Walter?

71
00:08:48,968 --> 00:08:51,079
Why did I not stay in a hotel?

72
00:09:13,310 --> 00:09:16,497
<i>Feel it burn .. and start to yearn</i>

73
00:09:17,271 --> 00:09:21,532
<i>to hold you tight</i>

74
00:09:23,794 --> 00:09:25,732
- Guess what, baby girl.
- What?

75
00:09:27,216 --> 00:09:29,042
-I am engaged.
-OK

76
00:09:29,263 --> 00:09:30,271
-He babe.

77
00:09:30,326 --> 00:09:33,161
- Isn't that a pretty sight?
- Careful it don't blind.

78
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,069
And...

79
00:09:38,077 --> 00:09:39,790
I'm not pregnant.

80
00:09:41,985 --> 00:09:44,883
Joe and I are settling down.
You and Darrel should follow suit.

81
00:09:45,065 --> 00:09:46,680
We could go away together on vacation.

82
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,844
Don't you know by now it doesn't happen with Darrel.

83
00:09:48,899 --> 00:09:51,618
I am getting tired of defending your reputation.

84
00:09:52,570 --> 00:09:54,605
I'm used to people talking behind my back.

85
00:09:55,835 --> 00:09:57,612
But if you did not accept who I am..

86
00:09:59,904 --> 00:10:01,318
that would really be tough.

87
00:10:01,803 --> 00:10:04,568
Hey, you're the best.

88
00:10:05,836 --> 00:10:07,630
And all the best people know it.

89
00:10:46,028 --> 00:10:47,598
Thank you

90
00:10:51,529 --> 00:10:53,129
Good luck. Thank you.

91
00:10:54,756 --> 00:10:57,848
- Would you like to play that all, sir?
- Sherman.

92
00:10:58,121 --> 00:11:00,118
All right Sherman, would
you like to play that all?

93
00:11:00,340 --> 00:11:02,582
Oh I'll rather play you off,
honey.

94
00:11:05,220 --> 00:11:07,494
Why don't you apologize to the lady, buddy.

95
00:11:08,533 --> 00:11:10,563
-Apologize, man.
-Sorry.

96
00:11:14,429 --> 00:11:15,819
That makes two of us.

97
00:11:16,401 --> 00:11:17,905
-Thanks.
-You're okay?

98
00:11:18,225 --> 00:11:19,307
Yeah.

99
00:11:39,315 --> 00:11:42,214
- A cup of tea?
- Frances!

100
00:11:43,696 --> 00:11:46,121
-Do you have any bourbon?
-Sure do.

101
00:11:47,427 --> 00:11:49,050
Matter of fact, I'll join you.

102
00:11:49,997 --> 00:11:52,129
Would not do you any harm to have several.

103
00:11:54,465 --> 00:11:56,198
It's the weather.

104
00:11:57,238 --> 00:11:59,613
Oh get myself out.

105
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,357
You sound like Cay.

106
00:12:03,147 --> 00:12:07,850
Locks herself in that cottage
and works until she drops.

107
00:12:08,428 --> 00:12:10,724
-What is she working?
-She sculpts.

108
00:12:16,568 --> 00:12:18,679
Oh, don't look at that stuff

109
00:12:19,484 --> 00:12:23,787
A lot of sentimental junk.
I have no taste.

110
00:12:26,843 --> 00:12:29,615
That is Glen, Cay's father.

111
00:12:30,687 --> 00:12:32,664
I had Walter by him.

112
00:12:34,402 --> 00:12:36,608
I'm not Cay's mother you know.

113
00:12:37,917 --> 00:12:39,570
I'm her ...

114
00:12:39,924 --> 00:12:41,823
I do not know what I am.

115
00:12:43,832 --> 00:12:45,730
Not anything really.

116
00:12:47,171 --> 00:12:50,303
A pair of hands and a familiar face.

117
00:12:52,499 --> 00:12:53,704
Thank you

118
00:12:55,712 --> 00:12:57,655
God, look at him.

119
00:12:58,416 --> 00:13:00,463
Handsome as day is long.

120
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:02,495
And married.

121
00:13:04,247 --> 00:13:06,428
I lived with him 10 years.

122
00:13:11,045 --> 00:13:14,967
Maybe I didn't get a bridal
bouquet to add to my collection.

123
00:13:15,090 --> 00:13:17,000
But I have what I wanted.

124
00:13:18,288 --> 00:13:20,282
I had a love of my own.

125
00:13:22,564 --> 00:13:24,445
That is a beautiful song.

126
00:13:26,570 --> 00:13:28,710
You had more than
most people dare hope for.

127
00:13:33,181 --> 00:13:35,509
Do not pay attention.

128
00:13:35,626 --> 00:13:37,525
I'm just babbling.

129
00:13:41,603 --> 00:13:43,680
I am a silly woman.

130
00:13:47,373 --> 00:13:49,339
I don't think you are a silly woman, Frances.

131
00:14:13,348 --> 00:14:14,246
Hi.

132
00:14:17,765 --> 00:14:20,302
You and me should make
a raisins and cream pie.

133
00:14:20,730 --> 00:14:23,761
-I'm too depressed.
-In this air?

134
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:26,292
She'll be be fine when she's rid of that creep.

135
00:14:26,443 --> 00:14:28,358
Larry is not a creep.

136
00:14:28,404 --> 00:14:31,783
Any man who leaves a woman
for a model is a creep in my book.

137
00:14:33,344 --> 00:14:34,860
I do not know which is worse.

138
00:14:35,031 --> 00:14:37,323
A cheater or a hobby man.

139
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,004
At least you can share
a hobby, Lucille.

140
00:14:41,939 --> 00:14:44,412
We would all like to
have a new past.

141
00:14:46,330 --> 00:14:47,996
Good morning!

142
00:14:48,328 --> 00:14:50,226
Good morning.

143
00:14:51,519 --> 00:14:54,133
-I come down to stretch my legs.
-It's was about time.

144
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:57,041
What have you been doing in
that room for the last five days?

145
00:14:57,590 --> 00:15:01,548
Whatever it is, it is too deep
for us to understand.

146
00:15:03,322 --> 00:15:05,695
Come, sit down.
Join the girl talk.

147
00:15:05,893 --> 00:15:08,163
We were discussing sex vs. marriage.

148
00:15:08,503 --> 00:15:12,803
No, I'm not an expert in either category
so I'll excuse myself.

149
00:15:12,905 --> 00:15:15,912
I heard that your culture types
go at it like banshees.

150
00:15:15,991 --> 00:15:18,484
- Lucille!
- Is that true?

151
00:15:19,381 --> 00:15:23,292
Actually banshees were folklore woman
wailing for the dead.

152
00:15:24,549 --> 00:15:26,291
Perhaps you meant
to say "monkeys".

153
00:15:27,088 --> 00:15:28,206
Hey!

154
00:15:30,215 --> 00:15:33,113
Well, I'll start with my pie.

155
00:15:34,695 --> 00:15:37,369
Lucille, would you drop Cays' mail by the cottage?

156
00:15:38,030 --> 00:15:39,466
I'll take it.

157
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:42,576
I'm going for a walk, anyway.

158
00:15:42,951 --> 00:15:45,742
Just slip it under the door.

159
00:15:50,651 --> 00:15:53,350
I mean you don't have to knock!

160
00:16:03,292 --> 00:16:05,557
- Morning!
- Morning!

161
00:16:25,037 --> 00:16:27,134
I was just passing by.

162
00:16:30,473 --> 00:16:32,371
Thanks.

163
00:16:36,780 --> 00:16:38,281
You want to come in?

164
00:16:39,531 --> 00:16:42,857
-I'd love to but you're busy.
-Come in anyway.

165
00:16:49,263 --> 00:16:52,044
To see if I can take it all
in one glance.

166
00:16:52,216 --> 00:16:54,464
Have a look around.

167
00:17:06,958 --> 00:17:08,962
I can't do it if you are watching me.

168
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,279
- Hi!
- Hi....!

169
00:17:18,007 --> 00:17:19,039
Hello

170
00:17:19,359 --> 00:17:22,840
-Where is Cay?
-I am here. You go back to sleep.

171
00:17:24,527 --> 00:17:25,996
Sorry. I was not alone.

172
00:17:26,102 --> 00:17:29,789
Fine. Socialization
was not what I had in mind, anyway.

173
00:17:40,009 --> 00:17:42,908
You get all that traffic
with no equipment ...

174
00:17:43,866 --> 00:17:45,637
beyond me.

175
00:18:12,793 --> 00:18:15,366
-Where are you off to?
-Lawyers appointment.

176
00:18:16,084 --> 00:18:17,974
No sense in taking two cars!

177
00:18:18,037 --> 00:18:20,476
-I do not want to intrude.
-Will you bring her back?

178
00:18:20,646 --> 00:18:23,473
Oh, don't worry about that.
Hop out, Gwen.

179
00:18:24,143 --> 00:18:27,452
You have a car for today
and save me a trip.

180
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:34,051
Cay, drive like a lady.

181
00:18:34,783 --> 00:18:37,266
Someone used it for an ashtray.
Come in up front.

182
00:18:44,103 --> 00:18:46,439
Long time without seeing you, Mrs. Parker.

183
00:18:47,471 --> 00:18:49,701
I'm handling it.

184
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:57,988
-Vivian, this is my friend, Gwen.
-From the cottage.

185
00:18:58,911 --> 00:19:00,749
Yes, nice to see you again.

186
00:19:17,899 --> 00:19:20,492
-Are you serious?
-About what?

187
00:19:20,812 --> 00:19:23,710
Listening to this funeral music for one.

188
00:19:24,457 --> 00:19:26,214
You know this piece, Vivian?

189
00:19:26,349 --> 00:19:30,525
Yes, it is Prokofiev. A suite for
three oranges. Lovely, isn't it?

190
00:19:31,349 --> 00:19:33,854
I better get to the record
store before they sell out.

191
00:19:34,221 --> 00:19:37,339
Oh, come on, Gwen.
We all have a sensitive side.

192
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:40,246
I do not recall you
mentioning that last night.

193
00:19:57,255 --> 00:19:59,588
-Thank you.
-Do you want me to wait?

194
00:19:59,744 --> 00:20:01,900
I am sure you have better
things to do than wait for me.

195
00:20:01,947 --> 00:20:03,642
Oh listen, I am sorry about the drive in.

196
00:20:03,697 --> 00:20:07,147
You know why I am here for.
I don't need to understand your friends.

197
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,919
I'll leave the key here.

198
00:20:08,993 --> 00:20:12,048
I have more important things to
think than how I'll go back.

199
00:20:12,235 --> 00:20:14,495
Oh, but thanks anyway!

200
00:20:14,606 --> 00:20:16,504
You're welcome.

201
00:20:20,817 --> 00:20:25,114
Here is from the agreement,
Dr. Bell is walking off with the whole store.

202
00:20:25,254 --> 00:20:27,226
I've always supported myself.

203
00:20:27,328 --> 00:20:29,574
Other than my books
there's nothing I want.

204
00:20:29,945 --> 00:20:31,411
-Is there a third party?

205
00:20:31,411 --> 00:20:32,411
No

206
00:20:34,142 --> 00:20:36,041
Rare women, walks out with no strings.

207
00:20:37,050 --> 00:20:38,950
What are your grounds?

208
00:20:41,282 --> 00:20:43,384
I have not practiced this.

209
00:20:46,121 --> 00:20:48,763
Well we are not the
easiest folks to talk to.

210
00:20:51,614 --> 00:20:53,670
-Are you enjoying the ranch?
-It's different.

211
00:20:55,895 --> 00:20:57,313
One bunch of coops out there.

212
00:20:57,357 --> 00:21:00,373
Mr. Warner, I'm 35 years old.
I want an honest life.

213
00:21:00,435 --> 00:21:03,383
I am leaving a decent marriage
to see if I can find one.

214
00:21:03,498 --> 00:21:04,699
Not having children helps.

215
00:21:04,708 --> 00:21:08,306
Although our careers served very
much the same purpose

216
00:21:08,315 --> 00:21:10,213
binding us together for all those years.

217
00:21:11,959 --> 00:21:13,653
We were very big on form.

218
00:21:14,561 --> 00:21:16,770
Right friends, right prints on the wall.

219
00:21:19,692 --> 00:21:23,928
I yearn for something we could not
analyze or reason away.

220
00:21:27,387 --> 00:21:30,335
I want to be free of who I've been.

221
00:21:30,844 --> 00:21:32,742
And your husband?

222
00:21:33,663 --> 00:21:36,460
Martin would be content to have
me with him regardless of how I feel.

223
00:21:36,659 --> 00:21:38,557
-He will not contest?
-No, no.

224
00:21:39,266 --> 00:21:40,364
Well...

225
00:21:42,473 --> 00:21:46,371
-We gotta go with mental cruelty.
-We've never treated each other with anything but....

226
00:21:46,477 --> 00:21:49,279
No, No. It's just an umbrella term.

227
00:21:50,056 --> 00:21:53,186
Nevada law prefers a headache or two

228
00:21:54,743 --> 00:21:57,072
Sure he refused to
visit in-laws, sometimes.

229
00:21:57,185 --> 00:21:59,501
Mr Warner, I may spend
the rest of my life alone...

230
00:22:00,724 --> 00:22:04,908
I made a very difficult decision and
it was not based on a headache or two.

231
00:22:10,296 --> 00:22:12,815
Martini time.
Would you have a drink with me?

232
00:22:14,264 --> 00:22:15,803
Please, go on.

233
00:22:17,542 --> 00:22:22,018
Well, the first thing I'm
obliged to advise my clients on

234
00:22:22,815 --> 00:22:25,537
is not leave the state
once the residency is established.

235
00:22:26,027 --> 00:22:29,444
A lot of folks leave for San Francisco
for a break.

236
00:22:29,453 --> 00:22:31,351
Don't misunderstand me, Mr. Warner.

237
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:33,597
But hell that wouldn't apply in this case.

238
00:22:34,768 --> 00:22:38,166
No. I trust we could leave the
keys with you any time.

239
00:22:41,982 --> 00:22:43,273
Thank you.

240
00:22:46,584 --> 00:22:49,580
Ok, put your stuff in here.

241
00:22:50,128 --> 00:22:53,113
Be sure to lock it.
And the change room is right over there.

242
00:22:53,558 --> 00:22:56,795
-Everybody. This is Joyce.
-Hi, Joy!

243
00:22:57,015 --> 00:23:00,640
I leave you here with the girls.
And I'll see you on the floor.

244
00:23:00,711 --> 00:23:01,810
OK

245
00:23:04,425 --> 00:23:08,048
Cay, I'll like to see you in my office
Please?

246
00:23:10,560 --> 00:23:13,106
Darrel, where shall I put the key?

247
00:23:13,256 --> 00:23:14,912
I'll tell you where to put it.

248
00:23:15,459 --> 00:23:17,239
Thank you, Silver.

249
00:23:18,247 --> 00:23:20,146
